# 📦 MOVED — the dictation tool code now lives in its own repo

The IT-dictation **code** was extracted out of this monorepo into a standalone **private**
repository on 2026-06-22. That repo is now the **single source of truth** for the code — all
bug-fixing, features, and the build colleagues run happen there.

**New repo:** `/Users/elias/Desktop/it-dictation` (local; private GitHub remote not yet created)

## What moved
The engine, pipeline, tests, vocab packs, the telemetry extension, the launcher, and the
`setup` script. Plus fresh public-safe docs (`README`, `CONTRIBUTING`, `ARCHITECTURE`,
`DEV-NOTES`).

## What deliberately stayed here (the private "brain")
Strategy and history that must **never** go public, even though the new repo is private today
(it's destined to go public — git history is forever):

- Product / GTM / pricing: `PRODUCT-VISION.md`, `MARKETING-VISION.md`, `GTM-CHANNELS.md`,
  `LAUNCH-TIMELINE.md`, `FREE-VS-PAID-LINE.md`, `RESEARCH-*.md`
- The overseer role + the running design narrative: `COUNCILOR.md`, `STATUS.md`,
  the `*-PLAN.md` family, `ROADMAP.md`, `ARCHITECTURE-SEAMS.md`, `BAKEOFF-RESULTS.md`
- The decisions log (`../../decisions/log.md`) and the AIOS memory

The `CONTRIBUTING.md` in the new repo carries **only** the General-vs-Personal vocab rule
(the contributor-facing slice of `PRODUCT-VISION.md`) — the commercialization plan stayed here.

## Working in this project from now on
- **Code / bugs / tests** => the new repo.
- **Strategy / decisions / vision** => here, in aios.
- The Councilor (advisory) work reads from here and briefs the coding agent that works in the new repo.
